ass=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLStyleElement\"><code>HTMLStyleElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTableCaptionElement\"><code>HTMLTableCaptionElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTableCellElement\"><code>HTMLTableCellElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTableColElement\"><code>HTMLTableColElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/API/HTMLTableElement\"><code>HTMLTableElement</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTableRowElement\"><code>HTMLTableRowElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTableSectionElement\"><code>HTMLTableSectionElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTemplateElement\"><code>HTMLTemplateElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTextAreaElement\"><code>HTMLTextAreaElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTimeElement\"><code>HTMLTimeElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTitleElement\"><code>HTMLTitleElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTrackElement\"><code>HTMLTrackElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLUListElement\"><code>HTMLUListElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLUnknownElement\"><code>HTMLUnknownElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLVideoElement\"><code>HTMLVideoElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HashChangeEvent\"><code>HashChangeEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/History\"><code>History</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageData\"><code>ImageData</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MessageChannel\"><code>MessageChannel</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MessageEvent\"><code>MessageEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MessagePort\"><code>MessagePort</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/API/Navigator\"><code>Navigator</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PageTransitionEvent\"><code>PageTransitionEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Plugin\"><code>Plugin</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PluginArray\"><code>PluginArray</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PopStateEvent\"><code>PopStateEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PromiseRejectionEvent\"><code>PromiseRejectionEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RadioNodeList\"><code>RadioNodeList</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ValidityState\"><code>ValidityState</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/API/Window\"><code>Window</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>\n\n<p>The <strong><code>Location</code></strong> interface represents the location (URL) of the object it is linked to. Changes done on it are reflected on the object it relates to. Both the <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/API/Document\"><code>Document</code></a> and <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/API/Window\"><code>Window</code></a> interface have such a linked <code>Location</code>, accessible via <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/API/Document/location\"><code>Document.location</code></a> and <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/location\"><code>Window.location</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> respectively.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>The <code>Location</code></em><em> interface doesn't inherit any property, but implements those from <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>URLUtils</code></a>.</em></p>\n\n<dl>\n <dt id=\"location.href_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/href\"><code>Location.href</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the entire URL. If changed, the associated document navigates to the new page. It can be set from a different origin than the associated document.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.protocol_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/protocol\"><code>Location.protocol</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the protocol scheme of the URL, including the final <code>':'</code>.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.host_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/host\"><code>Location.host</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the host, that is the <em>hostname</em>, a <code>':'</code>, and the <em>port</em> of the URL.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.hostname_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/hostname\"><code>Location.hostname</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the domain of the URL.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.port_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/port\"><code>Location.port</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the port number of the URL.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.pathname_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/pathname\"><code>Location.pathname</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing an initial <code>'/'</code> followed by the path of the URL.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.search_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/search\"><code>Location.search</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing a <code>'?'</code> followed by the parameters or \"querystring\" of the URL. Modern browsers provide <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/URLSearchParams/get#example\">URLSearchParams</a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/URL/searchParams#example\">URL.searchParams</a> to make it easy to parse out the parameters from the querystring.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.hash_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/hash\"><code>Location.hash</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing a <code>'#'</code> followed by the fragment identifier of the URL.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.username_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/username\"><code>Location.username</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the username specified before the domain name.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.password_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/password\"><code>Location.password</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the password specified before the domain name.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.origin_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/origin\"><code>Location.origin</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n <dd>Returns a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the canonical form of the origin of the specific location.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>The <code>Location</code></em><em> interface doesn't inherit any method<em>, but implements those from <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>URLUtils</code></a></em>.</em></p>\n\n<dl>\n <dt id=\"location.assign_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/assign\"><code>Location.assign()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Loads the resource at the URL provided in parameter.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.reload\"><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/API/Location/reload\"><code>Location.reload()</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Reloads the resource from the current URL. Its optional unique parameter is a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>Boolean</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, which, when it is <code>true</code>, causes the page to always be reloaded from the server. If it is <code>false</code> or not specified, the browser may reload the page from its cache.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.replace_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/replace\"><code>Location.replace()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Replaces the current resource with the one at the provided URL. The difference from the <code>assign()</code> method is that after using <code>replace()</code> the current page will not be saved in session <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/History\"><code>History</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, meaning the user won't be able to use the <em>back</em> button to navigate to it.</dd>\n <dt id=\"location.tostring_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Location/toString\"><code>Location.toString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Returns a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>DOMString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> containing the whole URL. It is a synonym for <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>URLUtils.href</code></a>, though it can't be used to modify the value.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// Create anchor element and use href property for the purpose of this example</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// A more correct alternative is to browse to the URL and use document.location or window.location</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> url <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">createElement</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'a'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nurl<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>href <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'https://developer.mozilla.org:8080/en-US/search?q=URL#search-results-close-container'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>href<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>      <span class=\"token comment\">// https://developer.mozilla.org:8080/en-US/search?q=URL#search-results-close-container</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>protocol<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// https:</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>host<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>      <span class=\"token comment\">// developer.mozilla.org:8080</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>hostname<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// developer.mozilla.org</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>port<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>      <span class=\"token comment\">// 8080</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>pathname<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// /en-US/search</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>search<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// ?q=URL</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>hash<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>      <span class=\"token comment\">// #search-results-close-container</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>origin<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// https://developer.mozilla.org</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specifications","title":"Specifications","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Specification</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Comment</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/browsers.html#the-location-interface\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML Living Standard<br><small lang=\"pl\">The definition of 'Location' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Living Standard</span></td>\n   <td>No change from <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/html52/\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"The 'HTML5' specification\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML5</a>.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/html52/browsers.html#the-location-interface\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML5<br><small lang=\"pl\">The definition of 'Location' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-rec\">Recommendation</span></td>\n   <td>Initial definition.</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Location","dataURL":"/pl/docs/Web/API/Location/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li>Two methods creating such an object: <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/location\"><code>Window.location</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> and <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/API/Document/location\"><code>Document.location</code></a>.</li>\n <li>URL related interfaces: <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/URL\"><code>URL</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/URLSearchParams\"><code>URLSearchParams</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> and <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The Location interface represents the location (URL) of the object it is linked to. Changes done on it are reflected on the object it relates to. Both the Document and Window interface have such a linked Location, accessible via Document.location and Window.location (en-US) respectively.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Location","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Location","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Location","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Location","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Location","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Location","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Location","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Location","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"pl/web/api/location","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/pl/web/api/location/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/pl/docs/Web","title":"Technologie Internetowe dla developerów"},{"uri":"/pl/docs/Web/API","title":"Lista Web API"},{"uri":"/pl/docs/Web/API/Location","title":"Location"}],"pageTitle":"Location - Lista Web API | MDN","noIndexing":false}}